cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with resource allocation for device-to-device (D2D) communications in wireless networks, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also proposes algorithms for solving the resource allocation problem, which involves machine learning techniques such as multi-armed bandit and adversarial bandit, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper includes simulation results that involve multimedia (cs.MM) elements such as graphs and charts.
